parameters:
"Selphie-san!! Is it true that there was a message from Tina
Onee-san?!"

"Yes, it was right at the deadline. We received confirmation
of mission completion from the town beyond the cave."

"It was reported that Maroges was not involved with the
human trafficking organization."

With a relieved sigh, Suelle's tension eased, but the
atmosphere between the two remained tense.

"She said she was heading to Maroges' place and since then,
there's been no contact. It seems her whereabouts are
unknown..."

"Yes, it's the same situation as the women who went to
confront the human trafficking themselves..."

An unpleasant air drifted through Suelle and the others'
room.

"I'm going to head to the neighboring town where Maroges is
now."

In the midst of the unsettling atmosphere, Selphie proposed
a plan.

"Isn't that dangerous? Even Tina, of all people, has gone
missing in this situation."

Suelle also shared the same concern. The possibility of
Selphie also... was an unavoidable thought.
"I know. But I possess skills in espionage as well."
Selphie, like Tina, has her own unique skills.

One such skill is stealth, which allows her to avoid
detection by enemy range scouting abilities.

And even if the enemy is beyond a wall, she has a top-class
range scouting skill that can pinpoint their exact location.

Selphie's weapon of choice is a gun. Furthermore, she can
create and load bullets with her skills.

The bullets she creates can ricochet off walls or penetrate
defensive spells, exhibiting various effects and even taking
down enemies behind barriers.
It was a unique skill that maximized Selphie's abilities.

"I'll move without being noticed, assuming escape as a
priority, and never initiate an attack."

"Besides, unlike Tina, I won't be making direct contact with
Maroges."

"Even if I find a trace, I won't pursue it deeply. I'll wrap
up and contact Suelle and the others on the same day. How
does that sound?"
"Wait, if Selphie-san is going, then I'm coming too!!"
Selphie waves her hand to stop Suelle, who is eager to go.
"No. If we all get captured, who will report back?"

"I'll go ahead to investigate, and then coordinate with Rise
and the legal department to capture the enemy. This is the
least risky approach."

Suelle understood. Selphie, with her unique skills, was less
at risk when operating alone.

On the contrary, Suelle accompanying her would likely be a
hindrance and increase the danger.

However, it was frustrating to be unable to do anything
while an ally was risking danger, especially with Tina
already missing.

Suppressing his feelings and in order to increase the
success rate, Suelle reluctantly agrees to the proposal.

"Considering what happened with Tina, if we don't hear from
Selphie once a day"

"Then we won't wait like we did with Tina; we'll head there
without question."

Truthfully, they wanted to stop Selphie from going, but
doing nothing would also mean losing the chance to save
Tina.
Rise probably feels the same dilemma.
"Yes, that would give me peace of mind."

"If we act now, we can still pick up on Tina's trail. But
the longer it takes, the harder it will be to track her
down."

"As long as she doesn't meet Maroges directly, I think
Selphie, who can avoid detection, will be safe."

"There's no point in worrying about it here. We'll do what
we can do."
"Who is this man? This is Selphie's room."

"Ri-Rise!! This man is the most important person in the
legal department!!"

"Ah!! So you're Mr. Misokasu!!? My apologies, I thought you
were a suspicious person."

"It's fine. As long as you understand. And I'm not Misokasu,
I'm Gugukas."

"No, no, don't worry about it. I'm often mistaken for a
suspicious person."

"Oops, I got a bit self-deprecating there. I came here today
because I have business with Selphie-chan."
He looks around, confirming that she isn't there.

"Selphie left a little while ago to conduct an
investigation."
"By investigation, you mean it's about Tina-chan, right?"

Gugukas is the head of legal affairs. Naturally, he must
have been informed by Selphie about the case.

"I'm sorry, it's all because I suggested it... If only I had
paid more attention to Maroges..."
Gugukas shows an exaggeratedly disheartened expression.

"We never anticipated that something like this would happen
to Tina."
"So? What do you need? If it's urgent, I can listen to it."

After glancing at the two of them, he shows a hesitant
demeanor. His attitude suggests that it's a matter of great
importance.

"Certainly, I could entrust the task to the two of you, who
are former hero members just like Selphie-chan."

With that, Gugukas begins to discuss the serious matter he
came for with a grave expression.

"Actually, we intercepted data that was sent towards
Maroges' mansion..."

"The content of the intercepted data seems to be some kind
of video data."
"Some kind of video? You couldn't figure out what it was?"

"We did look into it... but it seems that we can't
understand it unless it goes through the decryption device
in Maroges' mansion."

"It's a common but highly secure encryption method where
incomplete data is interpolated by a machine to form a
complete set."

"Yes, and about the content of the data... It was
transmitted and saved at this timing. And with a person as
significant as Tina-chan disappearing..."

"I believe there's a high possibility that it could be a
clue."

"Yes, and I would have preferred to ask Selphie-chan,
but..."

Maroges then takes out a memory-type device and shows it to
the two of them.

"I want you to infiltrate Maroges' mansion and analyze this
information through the decryption device there."

"I see. So that's why you came to ask Selphie, who has
infiltration skills."

"But Suelle and I don't have the same level of infiltration
skills as Selphie, and it could get complicated if we're
spotted by someone in the mansion, right?"

"You don't have to worry about that. Actually, right now,
there's no one in Maroges' mansion, not even the servants."

"It's possible that Maroges is planning to abandon that
mansion."

"Indeed, it's hard to imagine Maroges returning to the
mansion under these circumstances."

"Yes, but since he sent the video data to the mansion, I
think he originally planned to return once, analyze the
data, and then escape from the mansion."

"However, I believe he abandoned the mansion without
returning because he realized that our legal department was
already watching."

"It's unlikely that Maroges told his servants about the
analysis device."
"Bad things can leak from anywhere, after all."

"But if that's the case, I'm betting that the analysis
device somewhere in the mansion hasn't been discarded yet."

"I'd like you to find the analysis device in place of
Selphie-chan and analyze the data for us."

"If it's just an analysis device... yeah, I think I can use
it right away if I find it. I'll take over for Selphie."

"Oh, you'll take it on? Then one more thing. The mansion may
be unmanned, but I think a noble's mansion will always have
some kind of autonomous defense system."

"Especially a mansion like Maroges', where shady dealings
are happening."
"Rise-chan, could you also accompany Suelle as his escort?"

"With Rise-chan there, the defense system shouldn't be a
problem either."

"I'll jam their communications so your movements won't be
detected. Even if you engage the defense systems inside,
Maroges won't be notified, so don't worry."

"That's a relief. It's faster to just destroy them and move
on if they attack."
"Heheh, you're reliable this time for sure."
"Well then, I'm counting on you both, okay?"
You received a \C[2]Mysterious Memory\C[0] from Gugukas.
